# release-test

A minimal test Python package used to experiment with branch-based release workflows and automatic versioning via `setuptools_scm`.

## Purpose

This repository is intentionally small so you can validate how version numbers are derived from git tags/branch state and how release automation behaves across branches.

## Repository structure

```text
.
├── pyproject.toml            # Packaging + setuptools_scm configuration
├── README.md                 # Project purpose and structure
└── src/
    └── release_test/
        └── __init__.py       # Package module exposing __version__
```

## Versioning notes

- The package version is dynamic (`dynamic = ["version"]`).
- `setuptools_scm` reads git metadata (tags/commits/branch context) to compute versions.
- Installing/building from different branch/tag states helps verify your release strategy.
